Create keypair
use putty gen to create private and public key pair

https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSEC2/latest/UserGuide/managing-users.html

$ sudo adduser username

for ubuntu

sudo adduser username --disabled-password

sudo su -username

[newuser ~]$ mkdir .ssh
[newuser ~]$ chmod 700 .ssh

[newuser ~]$ touch .ssh/authorized_keys
[newuser ~]$ chmod 600 .ssh/authorized_keys

copy and paste public key 
NOTE: MAKE sure the key pair text start with ssh  , other wise you will get server refused key error while loggin in with new user 


Remove password

 $ sudo passwd -d test
 Removing password for user test.
 passwd: Success
 $ su test
 $ whoami
 
 

to delete user account

sudo userdel -r olduser

compgen -u
Will lists all users.

